model.stellar_models.test_core__operatio.name: test_core__operations_recent
model.stellar_models.test_core__operatio.raw_code:
{{ config (
    materialized = 'view',
    tags = ['recent_test']
) }}

WITH last_3_days AS (

    SELECT
        closed_at
    FROM
        {{ ref("_max_ledger_by_date") }}
        qualify ROW_NUMBER() over (
            ORDER BY
                closed_at DESC
        ) = 3
)
SELECT
    *
FROM
    {{ ref('core__fact_operations') }}
WHERE
    closed_at :: DATE >= (
        SELECT
            closed_at
        FROM
            last_3_days
    )

model.stellar_models.streamline__ledgers.name: streamline__ledgers

model.stellar_models._max_ledger_by_date.name: _max_ledger_by_date
model.stellar_models._max_ledger_by_date.raw_code:
{{ config (
    materialized = "ephemeral",
    unique_key = "closed_at",
) }}

WITH base AS (

    SELECT
        closed_at :: DATE AS closed_at,
        MAX(sequence) AS sequence
    FROM
        {{ ref("silver__ledgers") }}
    GROUP BY
        closed_at :: DATE
)
SELECT
    closed_at,
    sequence
FROM
    base
WHERE
    closed_at <> (
        SELECT
            MAX(closed_at)
        FROM
            base
    )

model.stellar_models.streamline__chainhe.name: streamline__chainhead
model.stellar_models.streamline__chainhe.raw_code:
{{ config (
    materialized = "view",
    tags = ['streamline_view']
) }}

WITH res AS (

    SELECT
        {{ target.database }}.live.udf_api(
            'POST',
            '{Service}/{Authentication}',
            OBJECT_CONSTRUCT(
                'Content-Type',
                'application/json',
                'fsc-quantum-state',
                'livequery'
            ),
            OBJECT_CONSTRUCT(
                'id',
                0,
                'jsonrpc',
                '2.0',
                'method',
                'getLatestLedger'
            ),
            'Vault/prod/stellar/quicknode/mainnet'
        ) :data :result AS DATA
)
SELECT
    DATA :id :: STRING AS ledger_id,
    DATA :protocolVersion :: INT AS protocol_version,
    DATA :sequence :: INT AS SEQUENCE
FROM
    res

model.stellar_models.streamline__chain_h.name: streamline__chain_head_tail
model.stellar_models.streamline__chain_h.raw_code:
{{ config (
    materialized = "view",
    tags = ['streamline_view']
) }}

WITH head AS (

    SELECT
        {{ target.database }}.live.udf_api(
            'GET',
            '{Service}/{Authentication}/ledgers?limit=1&order=desc',
            OBJECT_CONSTRUCT(
                'fsc-quantum-state',
                'livequery'
            ),
            OBJECT_CONSTRUCT(),
            'Vault/prod/stellar/quicknode/mainnet'
        ) :data :_embedded :records [0] AS DATA,
        DATA :sequence :: INT AS SEQUENCE,
        DATA :closed_at :: datetime AS block_timestamp
),
tail AS (
    SELECT
        {{ target.database }}.live.udf_api(
            'GET',
            '{Service}/{Authentication}/ledgers?limit=1&order=asc',
            OBJECT_CONSTRUCT(
                'fsc-quantum-state',
                'livequery'
            ),
            OBJECT_CONSTRUCT(),
            'Vault/prod/stellar/quicknode/mainnet'
        ) :data :_embedded :records [0] AS DATA,
        DATA :sequence :: INT AS SEQUENCE,
        DATA :closed_at :: datetime AS block_timestamp
)
SELECT
    A.sequence AS head_sequence,
    A.block_timestamp AS head_block_timestamp,
    b.sequence AS tail_sequence,
    b.block_timestamp AS tail_block_timestamp
FROM
    head A
    JOIN tail b

model.stellar_models.streamline__ledgers.name: streamline__ledgers_realtime
model.stellar_models.streamline__ledgers.raw_code:
{{ config (
    materialized = "view",
    post_hook = fsc_utils.if_data_call_function_v2(
        func = 'streamline.udf_bulk_rest_api_v2',
        target = "{{this.schema}}.{{this.identifier}}",
        params ={ "external_table" :"streamline_ledgers",
        "sql_limit" :"10000",
        "producer_batch_size" :"10000",
        "worker_batch_size" :"5000",
        "sql_source" :"{{this.identifier}}",
        "order_by_column": "sequence" }
    )
) }}

WITH ledgers AS (

    SELECT
        SEQUENCE
    FROM
        {{ ref("streamline__ledgers") }}
    EXCEPT
    SELECT
        SEQUENCE
    FROM
        {{ ref("streamline__ledgers_complete") }}
)
SELECT
    SEQUENCE,
    ROUND(
        SEQUENCE,
        -4
    ) :: INT AS partition_key,
    {{ target.database }}.live.udf_api(
        'GET',
        '{Service}/{Authentication}/ledgers/' || SEQUENCE,
        OBJECT_CONSTRUCT(),
        OBJECT_CONSTRUCT(),
        'Vault/prod/stellar/quicknode/mainnet'
    ) AS request
FROM
    ledgers

ASSET_ID.name: ASSET_ID

model.stellar_models.price__ez_asset_met.raw_code:
{{ config(
    materialized = 'incremental',
    incremental_strategy = 'merge',
    merge_exclude_columns = ["inserted_timestamp"],
    unique_key = 'ez_asset_metadata_id',
    post_hook = "ALTER TABLE {{ this }} ADD SEARCH OPTIMIZATION ON EQUALITY(asset_issuer, asset_code, asset_id, symbol, name)",
    tags = ['gold_prices','scheduled_core']
) }}

SELECT
    provider_asset_id,
    asset_issuer,
    asset_code,
    asset_id,
    NAME,
    symbol,
    decimals,
    blockchain,
    FALSE AS is_native,
    COALESCE(
        is_verified,
        FALSE
    ) AS is_verified,
    is_deprecated,
    {{ dbt_utils.generate_surrogate_key(['complete_token_asset_metadata_id']) }} AS ez_asset_metadata_id,
    SYSDATE() AS inserted_timestamp,
    SYSDATE() AS modified_timestamp
FROM
    {{ ref('silver__complete_token_asset_metadata') }}

{% if is_incremental() %}
WHERE
    modified_timestamp > (
        SELECT
            COALESCE(MAX(modified_timestamp), '1970-01-01' :: TIMESTAMP) AS modified_timestamp
        FROM
            {{ this }})
        {% endif %}
        UNION ALL
        SELECT
            asset_id AS provider_asset_id,
            NULL AS asset_issuer,
            NULL AS asset_code,
            -5706705804583548011 AS asset_id,
            NAME,
            symbol,
            decimals,
            blockchain,
            TRUE AS is_native,
            is_deprecated,
            TRUE AS is_verified,
            {{ dbt_utils.generate_surrogate_key(['complete_native_asset_metadata_id']) }} AS ez_asset_metadata_id,
            SYSDATE() AS inserted_timestamp,
            SYSDATE() AS modified_timestamp
        FROM
            {{ ref('silver__complete_native_asset_metadata') }}

{% if is_incremental() %}
WHERE
    modified_timestamp > (
        SELECT

        FROM
            {{ this }})
        {% endif %}

    block_number_max,
    block_count,
    transaction_count,
    transaction_count_success,
    transaction_count_failed,
    unique_accounts_count,
    total_fees AS total_fees_native,
    ROUND(
        (
            total_fees / pow(
                10,
                7
            )
        ) * p.price,
        2
    ) AS total_fees_usd,
    core_metrics_hourly_id AS ez_core_metrics_hourly_id,
    s.inserted_timestamp AS inserted_timestamp,
    s.modified_timestamp AS modified_timestamp
FROM
    {{ ref('silver__core_metrics_hourly') }}
    s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('silver__complete_native_prices') }}
    p
    ON s.block_timestamp_hour = p.hour

{% if is_incremental() %}
WHERE
    s.modified_timestamp >= (
        SELECT
            MAX(
                modified_timestamp
            )
        FROM
            {{ this }}
    )
{% endif %}

model.stellar_models.core__ez_operations.description:
An aggregated convenience table that joins `core.fact_operations`, `core.fact_transactions`, and `core.fact_ledgers`.

Learn more about Stellar data structures: https://developers.stellar.org/docs/learn/fundamentals/stellar-data-structures

OP_SOURCE_ACCOUNT_MUXED.name: OP_SOURCE_ACCOUNT_MUXED
OP_SOURCE_ACCOUNT_MUXED.description: Muxed source account for the operation.

OP_ACCOUNT_ID.name: OP_ACCOUNT_ID
OP_ACCOUNT_ID.description: The address of the account. The address is the account's public key encoded in base32. All account addresses start with a 'G'.

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.description: Float representation of the amount of an asset sent/offered/etc.

ASSET.name: ASSET
ASSET.description: The asset available to be claimed in the form of "asset_code:issuing_address". If the claimable balance is in XLM, it is reported as "native"

ASSET_CODE.name: ASSET_CODE
ASSET_CODE.description: The 4 or 12 character code representation of the asset on the network.

ASSET_ISSUER.name: ASSET_ISSUER
ASSET_ISSUER.description: The account address of the original asset issuer that created the asset.

ASSET_TYPE.name: ASSET_TYPE
ASSET_TYPE.description: The identifier for type of asset code, can be an alphanumeric with 4 characters, 12 characters or the native asset to the network, XLM.

AUTHORIZE.name: AUTHORIZE
AUTHORIZE.description: Indicates whether the trustline is authorized.

BALANCE_ID.name: BALANCE_ID
BALANCE_ID.description: The balance id of the claimable balance.

CLAIMANT.name: CLAIMANT
CLAIMANT.description: The account address of the account which claimed the claimable balance

CLAIMANT_MUXED.name: CLAIMANT_MUXED
CLAIMANT_MUXED.description: If the account is multiplexed, the virtual address of the account which claimed the claimable balance

CLAIMANT_MUXED_ID.name: CLAIMANT_MUXED_ID
CLAIMANT_MUXED_ID.description: If the account is multiplexed, an integer representation of the muxed account which claimed the balance

CLAIMANTS.name: CLAIMANTS
CLAIMANTS.description: An unstructured field that lists account addresses eligible to claim a balance and the conditions which must be satisfied to claim the balance (typically time bound conditions)

DATA_ACCOUNT_ID.name: DATA_ACCOUNT_ID
DATA_ACCOUNT_ID.description: The account address of the account whose data entry is no longer sponsored

DATA_NAME.name: DATA_NAME
DATA_NAME.description: The name of the data entry which is no longer sponsored

BUYING_ASSET_CODE.name: BUYING_ASSET_CODE
BUYING_ASSET_CODE.description: The 4 or 12 character code representation of the asset being bought.

BUYING_ASSET_ISSUER.name: BUYING_ASSET_ISSUER
BUYING_ASSET_ISSUER.description: The account address of the original asset issuer for the buying asset.

BUYING_ASSET_TYPE.name: BUYING_ASSET_TYPE
BUYING_ASSET_TYPE.description: The identifier for type of buying asset code.

FROM_ACCOUNT.name: FROM_ACCOUNT
FROM_ACCOUNT.description: The account address from which the payment/contract originates (the sender account)

FROM_MUXED.name: FROM_MUXED
FROM_MUXED.description: If the account is multiplexed, the virtual address of the sender account

FROM_MUXED_ID.name: FROM_MUXED_ID
FROM_MUXED_ID.description: If the account is multiplexed, the integer representation of the virtual address of the sender account

FUNDER.name: FUNDER
FUNDER.description: The account address that funds a new account.

FUNDER_MUXED.name: FUNDER_MUXED
FUNDER_MUXED.description: If the account is multiplexed, the virtual address of the account funding the new account

FUNDER_MUXED_ID.name: FUNDER_MUXED_ID
FUNDER_MUXED_ID.description: If the account is multiplexed, the integer representation of the account funding the new account

HIGH_THRESHOLD.name: HIGH_THRESHOLD
HIGH_THRESHOLD.description: The sum of the weight of all signatures that sign a transaction for the high threshold operation. The weight must exceed the set threshold for the operation to succeed.

HOME_DOMAIN.name: HOME_DOMAIN
HOME_DOMAIN.description: The domain that hosts this account's stellar.toml file.

INFLATION_DEST.name: INFLATION_DEST
INFLATION_DEST.description: The account address specifying where to send inflation funds. The concept of inflation on the network has been discontinued

INTO_ACCOUNT.name: INTO_ACCOUNT
INTO_ACCOUNT.description: The account address receiving the deleted account's lumens.

INTO_MUXED.name: INTO_MUXED
INTO_MUXED.description: If the account is multiplexed, the virtual address of the account receive the deleted account's lumens

INTO_MUXED_ID.name: INTO_MUXED_ID
INTO_MUXED_ID.description: If the account is multiplexed, the integer representation of the account receiving the deleted account's lumens

LIMIT_AMOUNT.name: LIMIT_AMOUNT
LIMIT_AMOUNT.description: The upper bound amount of an asset that an account can hold

LOW_THRESHOLD.name: LOW_THRESHOLD
LOW_THRESHOLD.description: The sum of the weight of all signatures that sign a transaction for the low threshold operation. The weight must exceed the set threshold for the operation to succeed.

MASTER_KEY_WEIGHT.name: MASTER_KEY_WEIGHT
MASTER_KEY_WEIGHT.description: An accounts private key is called the master key. For signing transactions, the account holder can specify a weight for the master key, which contributes to thresholds validation when processing a transaction.

MED_THRESHOLD.name: MED_THRESHOLD
MED_THRESHOLD.description: The sum of the weight of all signatures that sign a transaction for the medium threshold operation. The weight must exceed the set threshold for the operation to succeed.

NAME.name: NAME
NAME.description: The key for a data entry in manage data operations.

OFFER_ID.name: OFFER_ID
OFFER_ID.description: The unique id for the offer.

PRICE.name: PRICE
PRICE.description: The ratio of selling asset to buying asset.

PRICE_R.name: PRICE_R
PRICE_R.description: Precise representation of the buy and sell price of the assets on an offer. The n is the numerator, the d is the denominator. By calculating the ratio of n/d you can calculate the price of the bid or ask.

SELLING_ASSET_CODE.name: SELLING_ASSET_CODE
SELLING_ASSET_CODE.description: The 4 or 12 character code representation of the asset being sold.

SELLING_ASSET_ISSUER.name: SELLING_ASSET_ISSUER
SELLING_ASSET_ISSUER.description: The account address of the original asset issuer for the selling asset.

SELLING_ASSET_TYPE.name: SELLING_ASSET_TYPE
SELLING_ASSET_TYPE.description: The identifier for type of selling asset code.

SET_FLAGS.name: SET_FLAGS
SET_FLAGS.description: Array of numeric values of flags set for a trustline.

SET_FLAGS_S.name: SET_FLAGS_S
SET_FLAGS_S.description: Array of string values of flags set for a trustline.

SIGNER_ACCOUNT_ID.name: SIGNER_ACCOUNT_ID
SIGNER_ACCOUNT_ID.description: The address of the account of the signer no longer sponsored

SIGNER_WEIGHT.name: SIGNER_WEIGHT
SIGNER_WEIGHT.description: The weight of the new signer.

SOURCE_AMOUNT.name: SOURCE_AMOUNT
SOURCE_AMOUNT.description: The originating amount sent designated in the source asset.

SOURCE_ASSET_CODE.name: SOURCE_ASSET_CODE
SOURCE_ASSET_CODE.description: The 4 or 12 character code representation of the source asset.

SOURCE_ASSET_ISSUER.name: SOURCE_ASSET_ISSUER
SOURCE_ASSET_ISSUER.description: The account address of the original source asset issuer.

SOURCE_ASSET_TYPE.name: SOURCE_ASSET_TYPE
SOURCE_ASSET_TYPE.description: The identifier for type of source asset code.

SOURCE_MAX.name: SOURCE_MAX
SOURCE_MAX.description: The maximum amount to be sent in source asset.

STARTING_BALANCE.name: STARTING_BALANCE
STARTING_BALANCE.description: The amount of XLM sent to newly created account.

TO_ACCOUNT.name: TO_ACCOUNT
TO_ACCOUNT.description: The address of the account receiving payment funds.

TO_MUXED.name: TO_MUXED
TO_MUXED.description: If the account is multiplexed, the virtual address of the account receiving the payment

TO_MUXED_ID.name: TO_MUXED_ID
TO_MUXED_ID.description: If the account is multiplexed, the integer representation of the virtual address of the recipient account

TRUSTEE_MUXED.name: TRUSTEE_MUXED
TRUSTEE_MUXED.description: If the issuing account address is multiplexed, the virtual address of the trustee

TRUSTEE_MUXED_ID.name: TRUSTEE_MUXED_ID
TRUSTEE_MUXED_ID.description: If the issuing account address is multiplexed, the integer representation of the virtual address of the trustee

TRUSTOR_MUXED.name: TRUSTOR_MUXED
TRUSTOR_MUXED.description: If the trusting account is multiplexed, the virtual address of the account

TRUSTOR_MUXED_ID.name: TRUSTOR_MUXED_ID
TRUSTOR_MUXED_ID.description: If the trusting account is multiplexed, the integer representation of the virtual address of the account

TRUSTLINE_ACCOUNT_ID.name: TRUSTLINE_ACCOUNT_ID
TRUSTLINE_ACCOUNT_ID.description: The address of the account whose trustline is no longer sponsored

VALUE.name: VALUE
VALUE.description: The value for a data entry in manage data operations.

CLEAR_FLAGS.name: CLEAR_FLAGS
CLEAR_FLAGS.description: Array of numeric values of flags cleared for a trustline.

CLEAR_FLAGS_S.name: CLEAR_FLAGS_S
CLEAR_FLAGS_S.description: Array of string values of flags cleared for a trustline.

DESTINATION_MIN.name: DESTINATION_MIN
DESTINATION_MIN.description: The minimum amount to be received in destination asset.

BUMP_TO.name: BUMP_TO
BUMP_TO.description: The new desired value of the source account's sequence number.

SPONSOR.name: SPONSOR
SPONSOR.description: The account address of the sponsor who is paying the reserves for this ledger entry.

SPONSORED_ID.name: SPONSORED_ID
SPONSORED_ID.description: The account address of the account being sponsored.

BEGIN_SPONSOR.name: BEGIN_SPONSOR
BEGIN_SPONSOR.description: The account address that initiated the sponsorship.

BEGIN_SPONSOR_MUXED.name: BEGIN_SPONSOR_MUXED
BEGIN_SPONSOR_MUXED.description: If the initiating sponsorship account is multiplexed, the virtual address.

BEGIN_SPONSOR_MUXED_ID.name: BEGIN_SPONSOR_MUXED_ID
BEGIN_SPONSOR_MUXED_ID.description: If the initiating sponsorship account is multiplexed, the integer representation of the virtual address.

AUTHORIZE_TO_MAINTAIN_LIABILITIES.name: AUTHORIZE_TO_MAINTAIN_LIABILITIES
AUTHORIZE_TO_MAINTAIN_LIABILITIES.description: Indicates whether the trustline is authorized for maintaining liabilities.

CLAWBACK_ENABLED.name: CLAWBACK_ENABLED
CLAWBACK_ENABLED.description: Indicates whether the asset can be clawed back by the issuer.

LIQUIDITY_POOL_ID.name: LIQUIDITY_POOL_ID
LIQUIDITY_POOL_ID.description: Unique identifier for a liquidity pool. There cannot be duplicate pools for the same asset pair. Once a pool has been created for the asset pair, another cannot be created.

RESERVE_A_ASSET_TYPE.name: RESERVE_A_ASSET_TYPE
RESERVE_A_ASSET_TYPE.description: The type of the first reserve asset.

RESERVE_A_ASSET_CODE.name: RESERVE_A_ASSET_CODE
RESERVE_A_ASSET_CODE.description: The code of the first reserve asset.

RESERVE_A_ASSET_ISSUER.name: RESERVE_A_ASSET_ISSUER
RESERVE_A_ASSET_ISSUER.description: The issuer of the first reserve asset.

RESERVE_A_MAX_AMOUNT.name: RESERVE_A_MAX_AMOUNT
RESERVE_A_MAX_AMOUNT.description: Maximum amount for first reserve asset deposit.

RESERVE_A_DEPOSIT_AMOUNT.name: RESERVE_A_DEPOSIT_AMOUNT
RESERVE_A_DEPOSIT_AMOUNT.description: Actual amount deposited for first reserve asset.

RESERVE_B_ASSET_TYPE.name: RESERVE_B_ASSET_TYPE
RESERVE_B_ASSET_TYPE.description: The type of the second reserve asset.

RESERVE_B_ASSET_CODE.name: RESERVE_B_ASSET_CODE
RESERVE_B_ASSET_CODE.description: The code of the second reserve asset.

RESERVE_B_ASSET_ISSUER.name: RESERVE_B_ASSET_ISSUER
RESERVE_B_ASSET_ISSUER.description: The issuer of the second reserve asset.

RESERVE_B_MAX_AMOUNT.name: RESERVE_B_MAX_AMOUNT
RESERVE_B_MAX_AMOUNT.description: Maximum amount for second reserve asset deposit.

RESERVE_B_DEPOSIT_AMOUNT.name: RESERVE_B_DEPOSIT_AMOUNT
RESERVE_B_DEPOSIT_AMOUNT.description: Actual amount deposited for second reserve asset.

MIN_PRICE.name: MIN_PRICE
MIN_PRICE.description: Minimum exchange rate for deposit operation.

MIN_PRICE_R.name: MIN_PRICE_R
MIN_PRICE_R.description: A fractional representation of the prices of the two assets in a pool. The n is the numerator (value of asset a) and the d is the denominator (value of asset b).

MAX_PRICE.name: MAX_PRICE
MAX_PRICE.description: Maximum exchange rate for deposit operation.

MAX_PRICE_R.name: MAX_PRICE_R
MAX_PRICE_R.description: A fractional representation of the prices of the two assets in a pool. The n is the numerator (value of asset a) and the d is the denominator (value of asset b).

SHARES_RECEIVED.name: SHARES_RECEIVED
SHARES_RECEIVED.description: Number of pool shares received for deposit.

RESERVE_A_MIN_AMOUNT.name: RESERVE_A_MIN_AMOUNT
RESERVE_A_MIN_AMOUNT.description: Minimum withdrawal amount for first reserve asset.

RESERVE_B_MIN_AMOUNT.name: RESERVE_B_MIN_AMOUNT
RESERVE_B_MIN_AMOUNT.description: Minimum withdrawal amount for second reserve asset.

SHARES.name: SHARES
SHARES.description: Number of shares withdrawn from pool.

RESERVE_A_WITHDRAW_AMOUNT.name: RESERVE_A_WITHDRAW_AMOUNT
RESERVE_A_WITHDRAW_AMOUNT.description: Actual withdrawal amount for first reserve asset.

RESERVE_B_WITHDRAW_AMOUNT.name: RESERVE_B_WITHDRAW_AMOUNT
RESERVE_B_WITHDRAW_AMOUNT.description: Actual withdrawal amount for second reserve asset.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.description: The transaction identifier containing this operation.

TYPE.name: TYPE
TYPE.description: The mechanism that calculates pricing and division of shares for the pool. With the initial AMM rollout, the only type of liquidity pool allowed to be created is a constant product pool.

BATCH_ID.name: BATCH_ID
BATCH_ID.description: String representation of the run id for a given DAG in Airflow. Takes the form of "scheduled__<batch_end_date>-<dag_alias>". Batch ids are unique to the batch and help with monitoring and rerun capabilities.

BATCH_RUN_DATE.name: BATCH_RUN_DATE
BATCH_RUN_DATE.description: The start date for the batch interval. When taken with the date in the batch_id, the date represents the interval of ledgers processed. The batch run date can be seen as a proxy of closed_at for a ledger.

CLOSED_AT.name: CLOSED_AT
CLOSED_AT.description: Timestamp when the ledger was closed and committed to the network. Ledgers are expected to close ~every 5 seconds.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.description: A clone of closed_at for join convenience.

LEDGER_SEQUENCE.name: LEDGER_SEQUENCE
LEDGER_SEQUENCE.description: The sequence number of the ledger.

TX_OPERATION_COUNT.name: TX_OPERATION_COUNT
TX_OPERATION_COUNT.description: Number of operations in the transaction.

MEMO_TYPE.name: MEMO_TYPE
MEMO_TYPE.description: Type of memo attached to transaction.

FEE_CHARGED.name: FEE_CHARGED
FEE_CHARGED.description: Actual fee charged for the operation.

LEDGER_HASH.name: LEDGER_HASH
LEDGER_HASH.description: The hex-encoded SHA-256 hash that represents the ledger's XDR-encoded form.

PREVIOUS_LEDGER_HASH.name: PREVIOUS_LEDGER_HASH
PREVIOUS_LEDGER_HASH.description: The hex-encoded SHA-256 hash of the ledger that immediately precedes this ledger.

TRANSACTION_COUNT.name: TRANSACTION_COUNT
TRANSACTION_COUNT.description: The number of successful transactions submitted and completed by the network in this ledger.

LEDGER_OPERATION_COUNT.name: LEDGER_OPERATION_COUNT
LEDGER_OPERATION_COUNT.description: Number of operations in the ledger.

TOTAL_COINS.name: TOTAL_COINS
TOTAL_COINS.description: Total number of lumens in circulation

FEE_POOL.name: FEE_POOL
FEE_POOL.description: The sum of all transaction fees

BASE_FEE.name: BASE_FEE
BASE_FEE.description: The fee (in stroops) the network charges per operation in a transaction for the given ledger. The minimum base fee is 100, with the ability to increase if transaction demand exceeds ledger capacity. When this occurs, the ledger enters surge pricing.

BASE_RESERVE.name: BASE_RESERVE
BASE_RESERVE.description: The reserve (in stroops) the network requires an account to retain as a minimum balance in order to be a valid account on the network. The current minimum reserve is 10 XLM.

MAX_TX_SET_SIZE.name: MAX_TX_SET_SIZE
MAX_TX_SET_SIZE.description: The maximum number of operations that Stellar validator nodes have agreed to process in a given ledger. Since Protocol 11, ledger capacity has been measured in operations rather than transactions.

PROTOCOL_VERSION.name: PROTOCOL_VERSION
PROTOCOL_VERSION.description: The protocol verstion that the Stellar network was running when this ledger was committed. Protocol versions are released ~every 6 months.

SUCCESSFUL_TRANSACTION_COUNT.name: SUCCESSFUL_TRANSACTION_COUNT
SUCCESSFUL_TRANSACTION_COUNT.description: The number of successful transactions submitted and completed by the network in this ledger

FAILED_TRANSACTION_COUNT.name: FAILED_TRANSACTION_COUNT
FAILED_TRANSACTION_COUNT.description: The number of failed transactions submitted to the network in this ledger. The transaction was still paid for but contained an error that prevented it from executing

SOROBAN_FEE_WRITE_1KB.name: SOROBAN_FEE_WRITE_1KB
SOROBAN_FEE_WRITE_1KB.description: The fee associated with writing 1KB of data to the Soroban ledger.The write fee is dynamic fee that grows linearly with the size of the ledger. The write fee for a given ledger is recorded in the ledger header and has a direct relationship to the bucketlist size of the ledger db.

NODE_ID.name: NODE_ID
NODE_ID.description: The id of winning validator node which is allowed to write transaction set to the network. The winning validator is decided by the network.

SIGNATURE.name: SIGNATURE
SIGNATURE.description: The signing hash of the validator node which writes the transaction set to the network.This signature ensures the integrity and authenticity of the ledger, confirming that it has not been tampered with.

TOTAL_BYTE_SIZE_OF_BUCKET_LIST.name: TOTAL_BYTE_SIZE_OF_BUCKET_LIST
TOTAL_BYTE_SIZE_OF_BUCKET_LIST.description: Total size in bytes of the bucket list

NON_REFUNDABLE_RESOURCE_FEE_CHARGED.name: NON_REFUNDABLE_RESOURCE_FEE_CHARGED
NON_REFUNDABLE_RESOURCE_FEE_CHARGED.description: The amount of the resource fee charged for the transaction that is non-refundable.

REFUNDABLE_RESOURCE_FEE_CHARGED.name: REFUNDABLE_RESOURCE_FEE_CHARGED
REFUNDABLE_RESOURCE_FEE_CHARGED.description: The amount of the resource fee charged for the transaction that is refundable.

RENT_FEE_CHARGED.name: RENT_FEE_CHARGED
RENT_FEE_CHARGED.description: The fee charged for renting resources on the network, such as storage space for data.

TX_SIGNERS.name: TX_SIGNERS
TX_SIGNERS.description: The public keys of the signers who authorized the transaction.

REFUNDABLE_FEE.name: REFUNDABLE_FEE
REFUNDABLE_FEE.description: The portion of the transaction fee that is refundable under certain conditions.

FACT_OPERATIONS_ID.name: FACT_OPERATIONS_ID
FACT_OPERATIONS_ID.description: Unique primary key for the dimension table, used as the main identifier for each record.

INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.description: Timestamp when this record was inserted.

MODIFIED_TIMESTAMP.name: MODIFIED_TIMESTAMP
MODIFIED_TIMESTAMP.description: Timestamp when this record was last modified.

_INVOCATION_ID.name: _INVOCATION_ID
_INVOCATION_ID.description: Unique identifier of the dbt job that inserted or modified this record.

model.stellar_models.core__ez_operations.raw_code:
-- depends_on: {{ ref('core__fact_operations') }}
-- depends_on: {{ ref('core__fact_transactions') }}
-- depends_on: {{ ref('core__fact_ledgers') }}
{{ config(
    materialized = 'incremental',
    unique_key = ['op_id'],
    cluster_by = ['block_timestamp::DATE', 'closed_at::DATE', 'type_string'],
    post_hook = "ALTER TABLE {{ this }} ADD SEARCH OPTIMIZATION ON EQUALITY(op_source_account,asset,asset_code,asset_issuer,buying_asset_code,buying_asset_issuer,selling_asset_code,selling_asset_issuer,tx_id,transaction_hash,ledger_sequence);",
    tags = ['scheduled_core']
) }}

{% if execute %}

{% if is_incremental() %}
{% set max_is_query %}

SELECT
    MAX(modified_timestamp) AS modified_timestamp
FROM
    {{ this }}

    {% endset %}
    {% set result = run_query(max_is_query) %}
    {% set max_mod = result [0] [0] %}
    {% set min_block_query %}
SELECT
    MIN(block_timestamp) AS block_timestamp
FROM
    (
        SELECT
            MIN(block_timestamp) AS block_timestamp
        FROM
            {{ ref('core__fact_operations') }}
        WHERE
            modified_timestamp >= '{{max_mod}}'
        UNION ALL
        SELECT
            MIN(block_timestamp) AS block_timestamp
        FROM
            {{ ref('core__fact_transactions') }}
        WHERE
            modified_timestamp >= '{{max_mod}}'
        UNION ALL
        SELECT
            MIN(block_timestamp) AS block_timestamp
        FROM
            {{ ref('core__fact_ledgers') }}
        WHERE
            modified_timestamp >= '{{max_mod}}'
    ) {% endset %}
    {% set min_bts = run_query(min_block_query) [0] [0] %}
    {% if not min_bts or min_bts == 'None' %}
        {% set min_bts = '2099-01-01 00:00:00' %}
    {% endif %}
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

WITH operations AS (
    SELECT
        id AS op_id,
        source_account AS op_source_account,
        op_source_account_muxed,
        account AS op_account_id,
        closed_at,
        block_timestamp,
        amount,
        asset,
        asset_code,
        asset_issuer,
        asset_type,
        authorize,
        COALESCE(
            balance_id,
            claimable_balance_id
        ) AS balance_id,
        claimant,
        claimant_muxed,
        claimant_muxed_id,
        claimants,
        data_account_id,
        data_name,
        buying_asset_code,
        buying_asset_issuer,
        buying_asset_type,
        from_account,
        from_muxed,
        from_muxed_id,
        funder,
        funder_muxed,
        funder_muxed_id,
        high_threshold,
        home_domain,
        inflation_dest,
        into_account,
        into_muxed,
        into_muxed_id,
        limit_amount,
        low_threshold,
        master_key_weight,
        med_threshold,
        NAME,
        offer_id,
        path,
        price,
        price_r,
        selling_asset_code,
        selling_asset_issuer,
        selling_asset_type,
        set_flags,
        set_flags_s,
        signer_account_id,
        signer_key,
        signer_weight,
        source_amount,
        source_asset_code,
        source_asset_issuer,
        source_asset_type,
        source_max,
        starting_balance,
        to_account,
        to_muxed,
        to_muxed_id,
        trustee,
        trustee_muxed,
        trustee_muxed_id,
        trustor,
        trustor_muxed,
        trustor_muxed_id,
        trustline_account_id,
        trustline_asset,
        VALUE,
        clear_flags,
        clear_flags_s,
        destination_min,
        bump_to,
        sponsor,
        sponsored_id,
        begin_sponsor,
        begin_sponsor_muxed,
        begin_sponsor_muxed_id,
        authorize_to_maintain_liabilities,
        clawback_enabled,
        liquidity_pool_id,
        reserve_a_asset_type,
        reserve_a_asset_code,
        reserve_a_asset_issuer,
        reserve_a_max_amount,
        reserve_a_deposit_amount,
        reserve_b_asset_type,
        reserve_b_asset_code,
        reserve_b_asset_issuer,
        reserve_b_max_amount,
        reserve_b_deposit_amount,
        min_price,
        min_price_r,
        max_price,
        max_price_r,
        shares_received,
        reserve_a_min_amount,
        reserve_b_min_amount,
        shares,
        reserve_a_withdraw_amount,
        reserve_b_withdraw_amount,
        transaction_id AS tx_id,
        TYPE,
        type_string,
        batch_id,
        batch_run_date,
        asset_balance_changes,
        PARAMETERS,
        parameters_decoded,
        FUNCTION,
        address,
        soroban_operation_type,
        extend_to,
        contract_id,
        contract_code_hash,
        operation_result_code,
        operation_trace_code,
        details_json,
        modified_timestamp,
        ledger_sequence
    FROM
        {{ ref('core__fact_operations') }}

{% if is_incremental() %}
WHERE
    block_timestamp >= '{{min_bts}}'
{% endif %}
),
transactions AS (

{% if is_incremental() %}

)

    operations o
    LEFT JOIN transactions t
    ON o.tx_id = t.tx_id
    LEFT JOIN ledgers l
    ON t.ledger_sequence = l.ledger_sequence

model.stellar_models.core__fact_operatio.description:
This table contains the lowest granularity of data avaiable to the network. It contains all details regarding operations that were executed as part of a transaction set. Be careful - the table contains both failed and successful operations. The details record will return varying information about an operation according to the operation type.

Learn more about Stellar operations: https://developers.stellar.org/docs/learn/fundamentals/transactions/operations-and-transactions

CLOSED_AT.name: CLOSED_AT
CLOSED_AT.description: Timestamp when the ledger was closed and committed to the network. Ledgers are expected to close ~every 5 seconds.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.description: A clone of closed_at for join convenience.

ACCOUNT.name: ACCOUNT
ACCOUNT.description: The account involved in the operation.

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.description: Float representation of the amount of an asset sent/offered/etc.

ASSET_CODE.name: ASSET_CODE
ASSET_CODE.description: The 4 or 12 character code representation of the asset on the network.

ASSET_ISSUER.name: ASSET_ISSUER
ASSET_ISSUER.description: The account address of the original asset issuer that created the asset.

ASSET_TYPE.name: ASSET_TYPE
ASSET_TYPE.description: The identifier for type of asset code, can be an alphanumeric with 4 characters, 12 characters or the native asset to the network, XLM.

ASSET_ID.name: ASSET_ID
ASSET_ID.description: The Farm Hash encoding of Asset Code + Asset Issuer + Asset Type. This field is optimized for cross table joins since integer joins are less expensive than the original asset id components.

AUTHORIZE.name: AUTHORIZE
AUTHORIZE.description: Indicates whether the trustline is authorized.

BALANCE_ID.name: BALANCE_ID
BALANCE_ID.description: The balance id of the claimable balance.

BUYING_ASSET_CODE.name: BUYING_ASSET_CODE
BUYING_ASSET_CODE.description: The 4 or 12 character code representation of the asset being bought.

BUYING_ASSET_ISSUER.name: BUYING_ASSET_ISSUER
BUYING_ASSET_ISSUER.description: The account address of the original asset issuer for the buying asset.

BUYING_ASSET_TYPE.name: BUYING_ASSET_TYPE
BUYING_ASSET_TYPE.description: The identifier for type of buying asset code.

BUYING_ASSET_ID.name: BUYING_ASSET_ID
BUYING_ASSET_ID.description: The identifier of the asset being bought.

FROM_ACCOUNT.name: FROM_ACCOUNT
FROM_ACCOUNT.description: The account address from which the payment/contract originates.

FUNDER.name: FUNDER
FUNDER.description: The account address that funds a new account.

HIGH_THRESHOLD.name: HIGH_THRESHOLD
HIGH_THRESHOLD.description: The sum of the weight of all signatures that sign a transaction for the high threshold operation. The weight must exceed the set threshold for the operation to succeed.

HOME_DOMAIN.name: HOME_DOMAIN
HOME_DOMAIN.description: The domain that hosts this account's stellar.toml file.

INFLATION_DEST.name: INFLATION_DEST
INFLATION_DEST.description: Deprecated: The account address to receive an inflation payment when they are disbursed on the network.

INTO_ACCOUNT.name: INTO_ACCOUNT
INTO_ACCOUNT.description: The account address receiving the deleted account's lumens.

LIMIT_AMOUNT.name: LIMIT_AMOUNT
LIMIT_AMOUNT.description: The upper bound amount of an asset that an account can hold.

LOW_THRESHOLD.name: LOW_THRESHOLD
LOW_THRESHOLD.description: The sum of the weight of all signatures that sign a transaction for the low threshold operation. The weight must exceed the set threshold for the operation to succeed.

MASTER_KEY_WEIGHT.name: MASTER_KEY_WEIGHT
MASTER_KEY_WEIGHT.description: The weight of the master key, which is the private key for this account. If a master key is '0', the account is locked and cannot be used.

MED_THRESHOLD.name: MED_THRESHOLD
MED_THRESHOLD.description: The sum of the weight of all signatures that sign a transaction for the medium threshold operation. The weight must exceed the set threshold for the operation to succeed.

NAME.name: NAME
NAME.description: The key for a data entry in manage data operations.

OFFER_ID.name: OFFER_ID
OFFER_ID.description: The unique id for the offer.

PRICE.name: PRICE
PRICE.description: The ratio of selling asset to buying asset.

PRICE_R.name: PRICE_R
PRICE_R.description: Precise representation of the buy and sell price of the assets on an offer. The n is the numerator, the d is the denominator. By calculating the ratio of n/d you can calculate the price of the bid or ask.

SELLING_ASSET_CODE.name: SELLING_ASSET_CODE
SELLING_ASSET_CODE.description: The 4 or 12 character code representation of the asset being sold.

SELLING_ASSET_ISSUER.name: SELLING_ASSET_ISSUER
SELLING_ASSET_ISSUER.description: The account address of the original asset issuer for the selling asset.

SELLING_ASSET_TYPE.name: SELLING_ASSET_TYPE
SELLING_ASSET_TYPE.description: The identifier for type of selling asset code.

SELLING_ASSET_ID.name: SELLING_ASSET_ID
SELLING_ASSET_ID.description: The identifier of the asset being sold.

SET_FLAGS.name: SET_FLAGS
SET_FLAGS.description: Array of numeric values of flags set for a trustline.

SET_FLAGS_S.name: SET_FLAGS_S
SET_FLAGS_S.description: Array of string values of flags set for a trustline.

SIGNER_ACCOUNT_ID.name: SIGNER_ACCOUNT_ID
SIGNER_ACCOUNT_ID.description: The address of the account of the signer no longer sponsored

SIGNER_WEIGHT.name: SIGNER_WEIGHT
SIGNER_WEIGHT.description: The weight of the new signer.

SOURCE_AMOUNT.name: SOURCE_AMOUNT
SOURCE_AMOUNT.description: The originating amount sent designated in the source asset.

SOURCE_ASSET_CODE.name: SOURCE_ASSET_CODE
SOURCE_ASSET_CODE.description: The 4 or 12 character code representation of the source asset.

SOURCE_ASSET_ISSUER.name: SOURCE_ASSET_ISSUER
SOURCE_ASSET_ISSUER.description: The account address of the original source asset issuer.

SOURCE_ASSET_TYPE.name: SOURCE_ASSET_TYPE
SOURCE_ASSET_TYPE.description: The identifier for type of source asset code.

SOURCE_ASSET_ID.name: SOURCE_ASSET_ID
SOURCE_ASSET_ID.description: The identifier of the source asset.

SOURCE_MAX.name: SOURCE_MAX
SOURCE_MAX.description: The maximum amount to be sent in source asset.

STARTING_BALANCE.name: STARTING_BALANCE
STARTING_BALANCE.description: The amount of XLM sent to newly created account.

TO_ACCOUNT.name: TO_ACCOUNT
TO_ACCOUNT.description: The address of the account receiving payment funds.

VALUE.name: VALUE
VALUE.description: The value for a data entry in manage data operations.

CLEAR_FLAGS.name: CLEAR_FLAGS
CLEAR_FLAGS.description: Array of numeric values of flags cleared for a trustline.

CLEAR_FLAGS_S.name: CLEAR_FLAGS_S
CLEAR_FLAGS_S.description: Array of string values of flags cleared for a trustline.

DESTINATION_MIN.name: DESTINATION_MIN
DESTINATION_MIN.description: The minimum amount to be received in destination asset.

BUMP_TO.name: BUMP_TO
BUMP_TO.description: The new desired value of the source account's sequence number.

SPONSOR.name: SPONSOR
SPONSOR.description: The account address of the sponsor who is paying the reserves for this ledger entry.

SPONSORED_ID.name: SPONSORED_ID
SPONSORED_ID.description: The account address of the account being sponsored.

BEGIN_SPONSOR.name: BEGIN_SPONSOR
BEGIN_SPONSOR.description: The account address that initiated the sponsorship.

AUTHORIZE_TO_MAINTAIN_LIABILITIES.name: AUTHORIZE_TO_MAINTAIN_LIABILITIES
AUTHORIZE_TO_MAINTAIN_LIABILITIES.description: Indicates whether the trustline is authorized for maintaining liabilities.

CLAWBACK_ENABLED.name: CLAWBACK_ENABLED
CLAWBACK_ENABLED.description: Indicates whether the asset can be clawed back by the issuer.

LIQUIDITY_POOL_ID.name: LIQUIDITY_POOL_ID
LIQUIDITY_POOL_ID.description: Unique identifier for a liquidity pool. There cannot be duplicate pools for the same asset pair. Once a pool has been created for the asset pair, another cannot be created.

RESERVE_A_ASSET_TYPE.name: RESERVE_A_ASSET_TYPE
RESERVE_A_ASSET_TYPE.description: The type of the first reserve asset.

RESERVE_A_ASSET_ID.name: RESERVE_A_ASSET_ID
RESERVE_A_ASSET_ID.description: The identifier of the first reserve asset.

RESERVE_A_ASSET_CODE.name: RESERVE_A_ASSET_CODE
RESERVE_A_ASSET_CODE.description: The code of the first reserve asset.

RESERVE_A_ASSET_ISSUER.name: RESERVE_A_ASSET_ISSUER
RESERVE_A_ASSET_ISSUER.description: The issuer of the first reserve asset.

RESERVE_A_MAX_AMOUNT.name: RESERVE_A_MAX_AMOUNT
RESERVE_A_MAX_AMOUNT.description: Maximum amount for first reserve asset deposit.

RESERVE_A_DEPOSIT_AMOUNT.name: RESERVE_A_DEPOSIT_AMOUNT
RESERVE_A_DEPOSIT_AMOUNT.description: Actual amount deposited for first reserve asset.

RESERVE_B_ASSET_TYPE.name: RESERVE_B_ASSET_TYPE
RESERVE_B_ASSET_TYPE.description: The type of the second reserve asset.

RESERVE_B_ASSET_ID.name: RESERVE_B_ASSET_ID
RESERVE_B_ASSET_ID.description: The identifier of the second reserve asset.

RESERVE_B_ASSET_CODE.name: RESERVE_B_ASSET_CODE
RESERVE_B_ASSET_CODE.description: The code of the second reserve asset.

RESERVE_B_ASSET_ISSUER.name: RESERVE_B_ASSET_ISSUER
RESERVE_B_ASSET_ISSUER.description: The issuer of the second reserve asset.

RESERVE_B_MAX_AMOUNT.name: RESERVE_B_MAX_AMOUNT
RESERVE_B_MAX_AMOUNT.description: Maximum amount for second reserve asset deposit.

RESERVE_B_DEPOSIT_AMOUNT.name: RESERVE_B_DEPOSIT_AMOUNT
RESERVE_B_DEPOSIT_AMOUNT.description: Actual amount deposited for second reserve asset.

MIN_PRICE.name: MIN_PRICE
MIN_PRICE.description: Minimum exchange rate for deposit operation.

MIN_PRICE_R.name: MIN_PRICE_R
MIN_PRICE_R.description: A fractional representation of the prices of the two assets in a pool. The n is the numerator (value of asset a) and the d is the denominator (value of asset b).

MAX_PRICE.name: MAX_PRICE
MAX_PRICE.description: Maximum exchange rate for deposit operation.

MAX_PRICE_R.name: MAX_PRICE_R
MAX_PRICE_R.description: A fractional representation of the prices of the two assets in a pool. The n is the numerator (value of asset a) and the d is the denominator (value of asset b).

SHARES.name: SHARES
SHARES.description: Number of shares withdrawn from pool.

RESERVE_A_WITHDRAW_AMOUNT.name: RESERVE_A_WITHDRAW_AMOUNT
RESERVE_A_WITHDRAW_AMOUNT.description: Actual withdrawal amount for first reserve asset.

RESERVE_B_WITHDRAW_AMOUNT.name: RESERVE_B_WITHDRAW_AMOUNT
RESERVE_B_WITHDRAW_AMOUNT.description: Actual withdrawal amount for second reserve asset.

SOURCE_ACCOUNT.name: SOURCE_ACCOUNT
SOURCE_ACCOUNT.description: The account that originated the transaction.

OP_SOURCE_ACCOUNT_MUXED.name: OP_SOURCE_ACCOUNT_MUXED
OP_SOURCE_ACCOUNT_MUXED.description: Muxed source account for the operation.

TRANSACTION_ID.name: TRANSACTION_ID
TRANSACTION_ID.description: The transaction identifier containing this operation.

TYPE.name: TYPE
TYPE.description: The mechanism that calculates pricing and division of shares for the pool. With the initial AMM rollout, the only type of liquidity pool allowed to be created is a constant product pool.

LEDGER_SEQUENCE.name: LEDGER_SEQUENCE
LEDGER_SEQUENCE.description: The sequence number of the ledger.

OP_ACCOUNT_MUXED_ID.name: OP_ACCOUNT_MUXED_ID
OP_ACCOUNT_MUXED_ID.description: Record that contains details based on the type of operation executed. Each operation will return its own relevant details, with the rest of the details as null

LEDGER_KEY_HASH.name: LEDGER_KEY_HASH
LEDGER_KEY_HASH.description: Hash of the ledgerKey which is a subset of the ledgerEntry. The subset of ledgerEntry fields depends on ledgerEntryType.

BATCH_ID.name: BATCH_ID
BATCH_ID.description: String representation of the run id for a given DAG in Airflow. Takes the form of "scheduled__<batch_end_date>-<dag_alias>". Batch ids are unique to the batch and help with monitoring and rerun capabilities.

BATCH_RUN_DATE.name: BATCH_RUN_DATE
BATCH_RUN_DATE.description: The start date for the batch interval. When taken with the date in the batch_id, the date represents the interval of ledgers processed. The batch run date can be seen as a proxy of closed_at for a ledger.

BATCH_INSERT_TS.name: BATCH_INSERT_TS
BATCH_INSERT_TS.description: The timestamp in UTC when a batch of records was inserted into the database. This field can help identify if a batch executed in real time or as part of a backfill. The timestamp should not be used during ad hoc analysis and is useful for data engineering purposes.

BEGIN_SPONSOR_MUXED.name: BEGIN_SPONSOR_MUXED
BEGIN_SPONSOR_MUXED.description: If the initiating sponsorship account is multiplexed, the virtual address.

BEGIN_SPONSOR_MUXED_ID.name: BEGIN_SPONSOR_MUXED_ID
BEGIN_SPONSOR_MUXED_ID.description: If the initiating sponsorship account is multiplexed, the integer representation of the virtual address.

CLAIMABLE_BALANCE_ID.name: CLAIMABLE_BALANCE_ID
CLAIMABLE_BALANCE_ID.description: The balance id of the claimable balance which is no longer sponsored

CLAIMANT.name: CLAIMANT
CLAIMANT.description: The account address of the account which claimed the claimable balance

CLAIMANTS.name: CLAIMANTS
CLAIMANTS.description: An unstructured field that lists account addresses eligible to claim a balance and the conditions which must be satisfied to claim the balance (typically time bound conditions)

CLAIMANT_MUXED.name: CLAIMANT_MUXED
CLAIMANT_MUXED.description: If the account is multiplexed, the virtual address of the account which claimed the claimable balance

CLAIMANT_MUXED_ID.name: CLAIMANT_MUXED_ID
CLAIMANT_MUXED_ID.description: If the account is multiplexed, an integer representation of the muxed account which claimed the balance

DATA_ACCOUNT_ID.name: DATA_ACCOUNT_ID
DATA_ACCOUNT_ID.description: The account address of the account whose data entry is no longer sponsored

DATA_NAME.name: DATA_NAME
DATA_NAME.description: The name of the data entry which is no longer sponsored

FROM_MUXED.name: FROM_MUXED
FROM_MUXED.description: If the account is multiplexed, the virtual address of the sender account

FROM_MUXED_ID.name: FROM_MUXED_ID
FROM_MUXED_ID.description: If the account is multiplexed, the integer representation of the virtual address of the sender account

FUNDER_MUXED.name: FUNDER_MUXED
FUNDER_MUXED.description: If the account is multiplexed, the virtual address of the account funding the new account

FUNDER_MUXED_ID.name: FUNDER_MUXED_ID
FUNDER_MUXED_ID.description: If the account is multiplexed, the integer representation of the account funding the new account

INTO_MUXED.name: INTO_MUXED
INTO_MUXED.description: If the account is multiplexed, the virtual address of the account receive the deleted account's lumens

INTO_MUXED_ID.name: INTO_MUXED_ID
INTO_MUXED_ID.description: If the account is multiplexed, the integer representation of the account receiving the deleted account's lumens

LEDGERS_TO_EXPIRE.name: LEDGERS_TO_EXPIRE
LEDGERS_TO_EXPIRE.description: The number of ledgers after which the operation will expire if its not executed.

OP_ACCOUNT_ID.name: OP_ACCOUNT_ID
OP_ACCOUNT_ID.description: The address of the account. The address is the account's public key encoded in base32. All account addresses start with a 'G'.

TO_MUXED.name: TO_MUXED
TO_MUXED.description: If the account is multiplexed, the virtual address of the account receiving the payment

TO_MUXED_ID.name: TO_MUXED_ID
TO_MUXED_ID.description: If the account is multiplexed, the integer representation of the virtual address of the recipient account

TRUSTEE_MUXED.name: TRUSTEE_MUXED
TRUSTEE_MUXED.description: If the issuing account address is multiplexed, the virtual address of the trustee

TRUSTEE_MUXED_ID.name: TRUSTEE_MUXED_ID
TRUSTEE_MUXED_ID.description: If the issuing account address is multiplexed, the integer representation of the virtual address of the trustee

TRUSTLINE_ACCOUNT_ID.name: TRUSTLINE_ACCOUNT_ID
TRUSTLINE_ACCOUNT_ID.description: The address of the account whose trustline is no longer sponsored

TRUSTOR_MUXED.name: TRUSTOR_MUXED
TRUSTOR_MUXED.description: If the trusting account is multiplexed, the virtual address of the account

TRUSTOR_MUXED_ID.name: TRUSTOR_MUXED_ID
TRUSTOR_MUXED_ID.description: If the trusting account is multiplexed, the integer representation of the virtual address of the account

FACT_OPERATIONS_ID.name: FACT_OPERATIONS_ID
FACT_OPERATIONS_ID.description: Unique primary key for the dimension table, used as the main identifier for each record.

INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.description: Timestamp when this record was inserted.

MODIFIED_TIMESTAMP.name: MODIFIED_TIMESTAMP
MODIFIED_TIMESTAMP.description: Timestamp when this record was last modified.

_INVOCATION_ID.name: _INVOCATION_ID
_INVOCATION_ID.description: Unique identifier of the dbt job that inserted or modified this record.

model.stellar_models.core__fact_operatio.raw_code:
-- depends_on: {{ ref('silver__operations') }}
{{ config(
    materialized = 'incremental',
    unique_key = ["id"],
    incremental_predicates = ["dynamic_range_predicate", "block_timestamp::date"],
    merge_exclude_columns = ["inserted_timestamp"],
    cluster_by = ['block_timestamp::DATE','closed_at::DATE','type_string'],
    post_hook = "ALTER TABLE {{ this }} ADD SEARCH OPTIMIZATION ON EQUALITY(source_account,asset,asset_code,asset_issuer,buying_asset_code,buying_asset_issuer,selling_asset_code,selling_asset_issuer);",
    tags = ['scheduled_core']
) }}

SELECT
    id,
    closed_at,
    closed_at AS block_timestamp,
    account,
    amount,
    asset,
    asset_code,
    asset_issuer,

model.stellar_models.core__fact_trust_li.description:
Trustlines track authorized and deleted lines of trust between an account and assets. This table can be viewed as a subentry to an account because all trustlines must be associated with a single account. The trust line also tracks the balance of the asset held by the account and any buying or selling liabilities on the orderbook for a given account and asset. You do not have to hold a balance of an asset to trust the asset.

Learn more about Stellar trust lines: https://developers.stellar.org/docs/data/analytics/hubble/data-catalog/data-dictionary/trustlines

account_id.name: account_id
account_id.description: The address of the account. The address is the account's public key encoded in base32. All account addresses start with a 'G'.

closed_at.name: closed_at
closed_at.description: Timestamp when the ledger was closed and committed to the network. Ledgers are expected to close ~every 5 seconds.

block_timestamp.name: block_timestamp
block_timestamp.description: A clone of closed_at for join convenience.

asset_id.name: asset_id
asset_id.description: The Farm Hash encoding of Asset Code + Asset Issuer + Asset Type. This field is optimized for cross table joins since integer joins are less expensive than the original asset id components.

asset_type.name: asset_type
asset_type.description: The identifier for type of asset code, can be an alphanumeric with 4 characters, 12 characters or the native asset to the network, XLM.

asset_issuer.name: asset_issuer
asset_issuer.description: The account address of the original asset issuer that created the asset.

asset_code.name: asset_code
asset_code.description: The 4 or 12 character code representation of the asset on the network.

liquidity_pool_id.name: liquidity_pool_id
liquidity_pool_id.description: Unique identifier for a liquidity pool. There cannot be duplicate pools for the same asset pair. Once a pool has been created for the asset pair, another cannot be created.

balance.name: balance
balance.description: The number of units of XLM held by the account.

trust_line_limit.name: trust_line_limit
trust_line_limit.description: The maximum amount of this asset that this account is willing to accept. The limit is specified when opening a trust line

buying_liabilities.name: buying_liabilities
buying_liabilities.description: The sum of all buy offers owned by this account for XLM only.

selling_liabilities.name: selling_liabilities
selling_liabilities.description: The sum of all sell offers owned by this account for XLM only.

flags.name: flags
flags.description: Denotes the enabling and disabling of certain asset issuer privileges.

last_modified_ledger.name: last_modified_ledger
last_modified_ledger.description: The ledger sequence number when the ledger entry was last modified. Deletions do not count as a modification and will report the prior modification sequence number.

ledger_entry_change.name: ledger_entry_change
ledger_entry_change.description: Code that describes the ledger entry change type that was applied to the ledger entry.

deleted.name: deleted
deleted.description: Indicates whether the ledger entry (account, claimable balance, trust line, offer, liquidity pool) has been deleted or not. Once an entry is deleted, it cannot be recovered.

ledger_sequence.name: ledger_sequence
ledger_sequence.description: The sequence number of the ledger.

ledger_key.name: ledger_key
ledger_key.description: The unique ledger key when the trust line state last changed

sponsor.name: sponsor
sponsor.description: The account address of the sponsor who is paying the reserves for this ledger entry.

batch_id.name: batch_id
batch_id.description: String representation of the run id for a given DAG in Airflow. Takes the form of "scheduled__<batch_end_date>-<dag_alias>". Batch ids are unique to the batch and help with monitoring and rerun capabilities.

batch_run_date.name: batch_run_date
batch_run_date.description: The start date for the batch interval. When taken with the date in the batch_id, the date represents the interval of ledgers processed. The batch run date can be seen as a proxy of closed_at for a ledger.

batch_insert_ts.name: batch_insert_ts
batch_insert_ts.description: The timestamp in UTC when a batch of records was inserted into the database. This field can help identify if a batch executed in real time or as part of a backfill. The timestamp should not be used during ad hoc analysis and is useful for data engineering purposes.

fact_trust_lines_id.name: fact_trust_lines_id
fact_trust_lines_id.description: Unique primary key for the dimension table, used as the main identifier for each record.

inserted_timestamp.name: inserted_timestamp
inserted_timestamp.description: Timestamp when this record was inserted.

modified_timestamp.name: modified_timestamp
modified_timestamp.description: Timestamp when this record was last modified.

model.stellar_models.core__ez_token_tran.description:
The token transfers raw table contains the SEP-41 compliant event stream from the token transfer processor. This table's purpose is to track the token value movement on the stellar network in the form of transfer, mint, burn, clawback, and fee events.

transfer, mint, burn, and clawback events are emitted at the operation grain. fee events are emitted at the transaction grain because there is no individual fee per operation.

fee events can be negative in the event of a refund. The final fee paid (intial fee + refund) will always be positive. More information about fee refunds can be found here.

Note that the events within this table are a subset of the events in the history_contract_events table.

transaction_hash.name: transaction_hash
transaction_hash.description: A hex-encoded SHA-256 hash of this transaction's XDR-encoded form.

transaction_id.name: transaction_id
transaction_id.description: A unique identifier for this transaction.

operation_id.name: operation_id
operation_id.description: A unique identifier for this transaction.

event_topic.name: event_topic
event_topic.description: The action type applied to the token.

from.name: from
from.description: The source address for the token transfer event amount.

to.name: to
to.description: The destination address for the token transfer event amount.

asset.name: asset
asset.description: ID field for the asset code/issuer pair. Its created by concatenating the asset code, ':' and asset_issuer fields.

asset_type.name: asset_type
asset_type.description: The identifier for type of asset code, can be an alphanumeric with 4 characters, 12 characters or the native asset to the network, XLM.

asset_code.name: asset_code
asset_code.description: The 4 or 12 character code representation of the asset on the network.

asset_issuer.name: asset_issuer
asset_issuer.description: The account address of the original asset issuer that created the asset.

amount.name: amount
amount.description: The normalized float amount of the asset in standard units. Raw stroop values are divided by 10,000,000 (10^7) to convert to human-readable token amounts. This conversion applies to all Stellar assets (XLM, BENJI, FOBXX, etc.) as the Stellar protocol uses 7 decimal places for all assets.

amount_raw.name: amount_raw
amount_raw.description: The raw stroop amount of the asset as stored on-chain. Stroops are Stellar's base unit (similar to wei in Ethereum or satoshis in Bitcoin), where 1 XLM = 10,000,000 stroops. This field preserves the exact on-chain representation before decimal adjustment.

token_is_verified.name: token_is_verified
token_is_verified.description: A flag indicating if the asset has been verified by the Flipside team.

ledger_sequence.name: ledger_sequence
ledger_sequence.description: The sequence number of this ledger. It represents the order of the ledger within the Stellar blockchain. Each ledger has a unique sequence number that increments with every new ledger, ensuring that ledgers are processed in the correct order.

closed_at.name: closed_at
closed_at.description: Timestamp in UTC when this ledger closed and committed to the network. Ledgers are expected to close ~every 5 seconds.

to_muxed.name: to_muxed
to_muxed.description: The multiplexed strkey representation of the `to` address.

to_muxed_id.name: to_muxed_id
to_muxed_id.description: The multiplexed ID used to generate the multiplexed strkey representation of the `to` address.

batch_id.name: batch_id
batch_id.description: String representation of the run id for a given DAG in Airflow. Takes the form of "scheduled__<batch_end_date>-<dag_alias>". Batch ids are unique to the batch and help with monitoring and rerun capabilities.

batch_run_date.name: batch_run_date
batch_run_date.description: The start date for the batch interval. When taken with the date in the batch_id, the date represents the interval of ledgers processed. The batch run date can be seen as a proxy of closed_at for a ledger.

batch_insert_ts.name: batch_insert_ts
batch_insert_ts.description: The timestamp in UTC when a batch of records was inserted into the database. This field can help identify if a batch executed in real time or as part of a backfill. The timestamp should not be used during ad hoc analysis and is useful for data engineering purposes.

model.stellar_models.core__ez_token_tran.raw_code:
-- depends_on: {{ ref('silver__token_transfers') }}
{{ config(
    materialized = 'incremental',
    unique_key = ["ez_token_transfers_id"],
    incremental_predicates = ["dynamic_range_predicate", "block_timestamp::date"],
    merge_exclude_columns = ["inserted_timestamp"],
    cluster_by = ['block_timestamp::DATE','closed_at::DATE'],
    post_hook = "ALTER TABLE {{ this }} ADD SEARCH OPTIMIZATION ON EQUALITY(transaction_hash,operation_id,from_address,to_address,contract_id,event_topic);",
    tags = ['scheduled_core']
) }}

SELECT
    transaction_hash,
    ledger_sequence,
    operation_id,
    closed_at AS block_timestamp,
    from_address,
    to_address,
    amount,
    amount_raw,
    amount * COALESCE(
        b2.price,
        b.price
    ) AS amount_usd,
    A.asset,
    A.asset_code,
    A.asset_issuer,
    A.asset_type,
    COALESCE(
        b.is_verified,
        b2.is_verified,
        FALSE
    ) AS token_is_verified,
    contract_id,
    event_topic,
    to_muxed,
    to_muxed_id,
    transaction_id,
    closed_at,
    batch_id,
    batch_run_date,
    batch_insert_ts,
    token_transfers_id AS ez_token_transfers_id,
    SYSDATE() AS inserted_timestamp,
    SYSDATE() AS modified_timestamp
FROM
    {{ ref('silver__token_transfers') }} A
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('price__ez_prices_hourly') }}
    b
    ON DATE_TRUNC(
        'hour',
        A.closed_at
    ) = b.hour
    AND A.asset_issuer = b.asset_issuer
    AND A.asset_code = b.asset_code
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('price__ez_prices_hourly') }}
    b2
    ON DATE_TRUNC(
        'hour',
        A.closed_at
    ) = b2.hour
    AND A.asset_type = 'native'
    AND b2.is_native
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('core__dim_assets') }} C
    ON A.asset_issuer = C.asset_issuer
    AND A.asset_code = C.asset_code

{% if is_incremental() %}
WHERE
    A.modified_timestamp >= (
        SELECT
            MAX(modified_timestamp)
        FROM
            {{ this }}
    )
{% endif %}

model.stellar_models.core__fact_daily_ba.name: core__fact_daily_balances
model.stellar_models.core__fact_daily_ba.description:
Daily snapshot of token balances for each account/asset combination on the Stellar network.
This model creates a complete daily time series by forward-filling the most recent balance 
when there's no activity on a given day. If multiple balance updates occur within a day, 
only the last balance of that day is retained.

Note: Currently filtered to verified tokens only. No automatic data retention policy applied - all historical data is preserved.

balance_date.name: balance_date
balance_date.description: The date for this balance snapshot (UTC)

account_id.name: account_id
account_id.description: The Stellar account address holding the asset

asset_issuer.name: asset_issuer
asset_issuer.description: The account that issued this asset ('native' for XLM) - uppercase normalized

asset_code.name: asset_code
asset_code.description: The asset code (e.g., USDC, 'native' for XLM) - uppercase normalized

balance.name: balance
balance.description:
The token balance at the end of the balance_date. 
Forward-filled from the most recent balance if no changes occurred.

is_deleted.name: is_deleted
is_deleted.description: Whether the trust line has been deleted (balance would be 0)

balance_changed_on_date.name: balance_changed_on_date
balance_changed_on_date.description: Boolean flag indicating if the balance actually changed on this date

daily_balance_change.name: daily_balance_change
daily_balance_change.description: The change in balance from the previous day

daily_balance_id.name: daily_balance_id
daily_balance_id.description: Unique identifier for this daily balance record

inserted_timestamp.name: inserted_timestamp
inserted_timestamp.description: Timestamp when this record was first inserted

modified_timestamp.name: modified_timestamp
modified_timestamp.description: Timestamp when this record was last modified

model.stellar_models.core__fact_daily_ba.raw_code:
{{ config(
    materialized = 'incremental',
    unique_key = ['daily_balance_id'],
    incremental_strategy = 'merge',
    merge_exclude_columns = ['inserted_timestamp'],
    cluster_by = ['balance_date::DATE'],
    tags = ['scheduled_daily']
) }}

WITH date_spine AS (

    SELECT
        date_day AS balance_date
    FROM
        {{ source(
            'crosschain',
            'dim_dates'
        ) }}
    WHERE
        balance_date < SYSDATE() :: DATE

{% if is_incremental() %}
AND balance_date >= (
    SELECT
        MAX(balance_date)
    FROM
        {{ this }}
)
{% else %}
    AND balance_date >= '2024-01-01'
{% endif %}
),

{% if is_incremental() %}
latest_balances_from_table AS (
    SELECT
        account_id,
        balance_date,
        UPPER(asset_issuer) AS asset_issuer,
        UPPER(asset_code) AS asset_code,
        balance,
        is_deleted
    FROM
        {{ this }}
    WHERE
        balance_date = (
            SELECT
                MAX(balance_date)
            FROM
                {{ this }}
        )
),
{% endif %}

ver_tokens AS (
    SELECT
        UPPER(asset_issuer) AS asset_issuer,
        UPPER(asset_code) AS asset_code
    FROM
        {{ ref('price__ez_asset_metadata') }}
    WHERE
        is_verified
),
source_data AS (
    SELECT
        *
    FROM
        (
            SELECT
                account_id,
                closed_at,
                closed_at :: DATE AS snapshot_date,
                A.asset_issuer,
                A.asset_code,
                balance,
                deleted
            FROM
                {{ ref('core__fact_trust_lines') }} A
                JOIN ver_tokens b USING (
                    asset_issuer,
                    asset_code
                )
            WHERE
                closed_at IS NOT NULL

{% if is_incremental() %}
AND closed_at :: DATE > (
    SELECT
        MAX(balance_date)
    FROM
        {{ this }}
)
{% endif %}
UNION ALL
SELECT
    account_id,
    closed_at,
    closed_at :: DATE AS snapshot_date,
    'native' AS asset_issuer,
    'native' AS asset_code,
    balance,
    deleted
FROM
    {{ ref('core__fact_accounts') }}

{% if is_incremental() %}
WHERE
    closed_at :: DATE > (
        SELECT
            MAX(balance_date)
        FROM
            {{ this }}
    )
{% endif %}
) qualify ROW_NUMBER() over (
    PARTITION BY account_id,
    asset_issuer,
    asset_code,
    snapshot_date
    ORDER BY
        closed_at DESC
) = 1

{% if is_incremental() %}
UNION ALL
SELECT
    account_id,
    balance_date AS closed_at,
    balance_date AS snapshot_date,
    asset_issuer,
    asset_code,
    balance,
    is_deleted AS deleted
FROM
    latest_balances_from_table
{% endif %}
),
account_asset_combinations AS (
    SELECT
        account_id,
        asset_issuer,
        asset_code,
        MIN(snapshot_date) AS first_seen_date
    FROM
        source_data
    GROUP BY
        account_id,
        asset_issuer,
        asset_code
),
daily_balances_with_gaps AS (
    SELECT
        d.balance_date,
        C.account_id,
        C.asset_issuer,
        C.asset_code,
        t.balance,
        t.deleted
    FROM
        date_spine d
        CROSS JOIN account_asset_combinations C
        LEFT JOIN source_data t
        ON C.account_id = t.account_id
        AND C.asset_issuer = t.asset_issuer
        AND C.asset_code = t.asset_code
        AND d.balance_date = t.snapshot_date
    WHERE
        d.balance_date >= C.first_seen_date
),
daily_balances_filled AS (
    SELECT
        balance_date,
        account_id,
        asset_issuer,
        asset_code,
        CASE
            WHEN LAST_VALUE(
                deleted ignore nulls
            ) over (
                PARTITION BY account_id,
                asset_issuer,
                asset_code
                ORDER BY
                    balance_date rows BETWEEN unbounded preceding
                    AND CURRENT ROW
            ) = TRUE THEN 0
            ELSE COALESCE(
                balance,
                LAST_VALUE(
                    balance ignore nulls
                ) over (
                    PARTITION BY account_id,
                    asset_issuer,
                    asset_code
                    ORDER BY
                        balance_date rows BETWEEN unbounded preceding
                        AND CURRENT ROW
                ),
                0
            )
        END AS balance,
        COALESCE(
            deleted,
            LAST_VALUE(
                deleted ignore nulls
            ) over (
                PARTITION BY account_id,
                asset_issuer,
                asset_code
                ORDER BY
                    balance_date rows BETWEEN unbounded preceding
                    AND CURRENT ROW
            ),
            FALSE
        ) AS is_deleted,
        CASE
            WHEN balance IS NOT NULL THEN TRUE
            ELSE FALSE
        END AS balance_changed_on_date
    FROM
        daily_balances_with_gaps
)
SELECT
    balance_date,
    account_id,
    asset_issuer,
    asset_code,
    balance,
    is_deleted,
    balance_changed_on_date,
    balance - LAG(
        balance,
        1,
        0
    ) over (
        PARTITION BY account_id,
        asset_issuer,
        asset_code
        ORDER BY
            balance_date
    ) AS daily_balance_change,
    {{ dbt_utils.generate_surrogate_key(
        ['account_id','asset_issuer','asset_code','balance_date']
    ) }} AS daily_balance_id,
    SYSDATE() AS inserted_timestamp,
    SYSDATE() AS modified_timestamp,
    '{{ invocation_id }}' AS _invocation_id
FROM
    daily_balances_filled
WHERE
    NOT (
        balance = 0
        AND is_deleted = TRUE
    )

{% if is_incremental() %}
AND balance_date > (
    SELECT
        MAX(balance_date)
    FROM
        {{ this }}
)
{% endif %}

This table contains all contract events, diagnostic events, and system events. Events cover a wide variety of information including token value movement, core metrics, and logging/debugging information.

Learn more about Stellar smart contracts: https://developers.stellar.org/docs/learn/fundamentals/stellar-data-structures/contracts

TRANSACTION_ID.name: TRANSACTION_ID
TRANSACTION_ID.description: The transaction identifier containing this operation.

CLOSED_AT.name: CLOSED_AT
CLOSED_AT.description: Timestamp when the ledger was closed and committed to the network. Ledgers are expected to close ~every 5 seconds.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.description: A clone of closed_at for join convenience.

LEDGER_SEQUENCE.name: LEDGER_SEQUENCE
LEDGER_SEQUENCE.description: The sequence number of the ledger.

IN_SUCCESSFUL_CONTRACT_CALL.name: IN_SUCCESSFUL_CONTRACT_CALL

fact_contract_events_id.name: fact_contract_events_id

INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.description: Timestamp when this record was inserted.

MODIFIED_TIMESTAMP.name: MODIFIED_TIMESTAMP
MODIFIED_TIMESTAMP.description: Timestamp when this record was last modified.

_INVOCATION_ID.name: _INVOCATION_ID
_INVOCATION_ID.description: Unique identifier of the dbt job that inserted or modified this record.

model.stellar_models.core__fact_contract.raw_code:
-- depends_on: {{ ref('silver__contract_events') }}
{{ config(

model.stellar_models.core__fact_transact.name: core__fact_transactions

post-hook.sql: ALTER TABLE {{ this }} ADD SEARCH OPTIMIZATION ON EQUALITY(id,transaction_hash,account);

model.stellar_models.core__fact_transact.description:
Transactions are commands that modify the ledger state and consist of one or more operations. In terms of taxonomy, a ledger contains a transaction set of multiple transactions, and a transaction contains an operation set of one to many operations. Transactions that are sent to the Stellar Network either succeed completely or fail completely. There is no partial transaction execution. The table is an event log of all transactions submitted and committed to a transaction set within a ledger.

Learn more about Stellar transactions: https://developers.stellar.org/docs/learn/fundamentals/transactions/operations-and-transactions

LEDGER_SEQUENCE.name: LEDGER_SEQUENCE
LEDGER_SEQUENCE.description: The sequence number of the ledger.

CLOSED_AT.name: CLOSED_AT
CLOSED_AT.description: Timestamp when the ledger was closed and committed to the network. Ledgers are expected to close ~every 5 seconds.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.description: A clone of closed_at for join convenience.

ACCOUNT.name: ACCOUNT
ACCOUNT.description: The account involved in the operation.

OPERATION_COUNT.name: OPERATION_COUNT
OPERATION_COUNT.description: The total number of successful operations applied to this ledger.

MEMO_TYPE.name: MEMO_TYPE
MEMO_TYPE.description: Type of memo attached to transaction.

FEE_CHARGED.name: FEE_CHARGED
FEE_CHARGED.description: Actual fee charged for the operation.

INNER_TRANSACTION_HASH.name: INNER_TRANSACTION_HASH
INNER_TRANSACTION_HASH.description: A transaction hash of a transaction wrapped with its signatures for fee-bump transactions

BATCH_ID.name: BATCH_ID
BATCH_ID.description: String representation of the run id for a given DAG in Airflow. Takes the form of "scheduled__<batch_end_date>-<dag_alias>". Batch ids are unique to the batch and help with monitoring and rerun capabilities.

BATCH_RUN_DATE.name: BATCH_RUN_DATE
BATCH_RUN_DATE.description: The start date for the batch interval. When taken with the date in the batch_id, the date represents the interval of ledgers processed. The batch run date can be seen as a proxy of closed_at for a ledger.

BATCH_INSERT_TS.name: BATCH_INSERT_TS
BATCH_INSERT_TS.description: The timestamp in UTC when a batch of records was inserted into the database. This field can help identify if a batch executed in real time or as part of a backfill. The timestamp should not be used during ad hoc analysis and is useful for data engineering purposes.

TX_ENVELOPE.name: TX_ENVELOPE
TX_ENVELOPE.description: A base-64 encoded XDR blob of the tx envelope (transaction and its signatures)

TX_RESULT.name: TX_RESULT
TX_RESULT.description: A base-64 encoded XDR blob of the tx result

TX_META.name: TX_META
TX_META.description: A base-64 encoded XDR blob of the tx meta

TX_FEE_META.name: TX_FEE_META
TX_FEE_META.description: A base-64 encoded XDR blob of the tx fee meta

NON_REFUNDABLE_RESOURCE_FEE_CHARGED.name: NON_REFUNDABLE_RESOURCE_FEE_CHARGED
NON_REFUNDABLE_RESOURCE_FEE_CHARGED.description: The amount of the resource fee charged for the transaction that is non-refundable.

REFUNDABLE_RESOURCE_FEE_CHARGED.name: REFUNDABLE_RESOURCE_FEE_CHARGED
REFUNDABLE_RESOURCE_FEE_CHARGED.description: The amount of the resource fee charged for the transaction that is refundable.

RENT_FEE_CHARGED.name: RENT_FEE_CHARGED
RENT_FEE_CHARGED.description: The fee charged for renting resources on the network, such as storage space for data.

TX_SIGNERS.name: TX_SIGNERS
TX_SIGNERS.description: The public keys of the signers who authorized the transaction.

REFUNDABLE_FEE.name: REFUNDABLE_FEE
REFUNDABLE_FEE.description: The portion of the transaction fee that is refundable under certain conditions.

FACT_TRANSACTIONS_ID.name: FACT_TRANSACTIONS_ID
FACT_TRANSACTIONS_ID.description: Unique primary key for the dimension table, used as the main identifier for each record.

INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.description: Timestamp when this record was inserted.

MODIFIED_TIMESTAMP.name: MODIFIED_TIMESTAMP
MODIFIED_TIMESTAMP.description: Timestamp when this record was last modified.

_INVOCATION_ID.name: _INVOCATION_ID
_INVOCATION_ID.description: Unique identifier of the dbt job that inserted or modified this record.

model.stellar_models.core__dim_assets.description:
Table reports which assets are used during the batch interval, which can help identify periods of time of large activity for an asset. The table does not have a primary key and assets are duplicated in the table as they are used during different periods of time. To get a distinct count of assets on the network, please refer to the history_assets table. Table not widely used.

Learn more about Stellar assets: https://developers.stellar.org/docs/learn/fundamentals/stellar-data-structures/assets

ASSET_ID.name: ASSET_ID
ASSET_ID.description: The Farm Hash encoding of Asset Code + Asset Issuer + Asset Type. This field is optimized for cross table joins since integer joins are less expensive than the original asset id components.

ASSET_TYPE.name: ASSET_TYPE
ASSET_TYPE.description: The identifier for type of asset code, can be an alphanumeric with 4 characters, 12 characters or the native asset to the network, XLM.

ASSET_CODE.name: ASSET_CODE
ASSET_CODE.description: The 4 or 12 character code representation of the asset on the network.

ASSET_ISSUER.name: ASSET_ISSUER
ASSET_ISSUER.description: The account address of the original asset issuer that created the asset.

ID.name: ID
ID.description: Numeric hash of asset_id, asset_type, and asset_issuer for join operations

DIM_ASSETS_ID.name: DIM_ASSETS_ID
DIM_ASSETS_ID.description: Unique primary key for the dimension table, used as the main identifier for each record.

INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.description: Timestamp when this record was inserted.

MODIFIED_TIMESTAMP.name: MODIFIED_TIMESTAMP
MODIFIED_TIMESTAMP.description: Timestamp when this record was last modified.
